msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/01"
msgid "Be quiet... We should be close to the British lines. They can hear you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/02"
msgid "Take them down quietly if possible. If they're here it means we're right next to the village."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/03"
msgid "Our objective is to secure Le Tôt - the village right next to us. After that, we will set up a bridgehead so our main force can arrive safely."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/04"
msgid "That's a British destroyer firing at us! They must have observers around here somewhere! We need to get rid of them!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/05"
msgid "Our main force has arrived. Now we are ready to push the remnants of the British forces back to the sea."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/06"
msgid "With enemy artillery observers watching our every move we cannot move out our tanks in the open. We need to send a small squad to eliminate the enemy forward observers and their radio operator."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/07"
msgid "After we make the enemy destroyer blind we will be able to use our tanks to neutralize enemy AA battery and call in our planes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/08"
msgid "Gute arbeit Soldaten! I'm giving you control of our armored vehicles and tanks."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/09"
msgid "Enemy AA battery neutralized. The Luftwaffe is now ready to deal with the enemy destroyer once and for all."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/10"
msgid "Our howitzer battery has just arrived. You also have access to airstrikes now. Use both of them to sink that floating piece of junk!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/11"
msgid "Good hit! The destroyer is neutralized!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/12"
msgid "Soldaten! Time for the last push! Let's throw the Tommies off the cliff! Their morale is low but they still have some dangerous units in their reserves."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_officer/13"
msgid "With the destroyer neutralized, the British soldiers had no chance of escaping! Secure their weapons, we've won another battle!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/01"
msgid "Scheiße... It's so foggy today. I can't see a thing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/02"
msgid "Halt! Two Tommies ahead! Verdammt..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/03"
msgid "They are running away!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/04"
msgid "What's that noise?... Sounds like artillery..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/05"
msgid "Enemy observers eliminated Herr Kommandant!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/06"
msgid "The enemy destroyer is targeting our troops! Move them quickly into cover before it fires!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/07"
msgid "One observer down! I think I see two more left!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/08"
msgid "Two observers down! There's only one left!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/09"
msgid "All enemy observers down!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[narrators]/ger_narrator_soldier/10"
msgid "The Engländer surrender! They have nowhere to run!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[reinforcements]/airstrike"
msgid "Airstrike"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[tasks]/task01"
msgid "Capture Le Tôt before the main force can arrive."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[tasks]/task02"
msgid "Eliminate enemy forward observers and radio operator to gain control of the tanks!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[tasks]/task03"
msgid "Neutralize enemy AA battery!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[tasks]/task04"
msgid "Neutralize the British destroyer!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[tasks]/task05"
msgid "Eliminate the remnants of the British forces on the outskirts of St. Valery en Caux!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/name"
msgid "Highlanders and Ghosts"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/name_big"
msgid "Highlanders and Ghosts"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/outro_completed"
msgid "Another encirclement won, and a second Dunkirk prevented! Your leadership will surely get you nominated for an iron cross sooner or later. Well done!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/outro_failed"
msgid "Dammit, we should have eliminated this pocket easily; what went wrong? We should have beaten these demoralized allied troops easily, now they might get away to England!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[tasks]/task_secret_01"
msgid "Secret objective #1"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/[tasks]/task_secret_01_completed"
msgid "Secret objective #1: Find a cave with hidden British equipment"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/date"
msgid "June 12th, 1940 · Saint-Valery-en-Caux, Normandy, France"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/place"
msgid "7th Panzer Division"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/051-ger_finesthour/1940_06_st_valery_en_caux/story"
msgid "The 7th Panzer, a.k.a. The “Ghost Division” passes Rouen on the 9th of June and makes for the coast the next day. Rushing to reach the coast, it has now closed the encirclement, successfully blocking the way out for several Allied divisions that are currently positioned in Valéry-en-Caux. \n\n Once more, we have successfully encircled an allied army - or what’s left of it.\n\n We can’t allow a second Dunkirk; you have to destroy the enemy before he has a chance to escape. Take the lead and advance immediately!"
msgstr ""
